p.seg: RB MSS M86B, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.

The list is one of a number sent by Cooke that are now in the library of the Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne. See notes to M. Cooke to M, 17 January 1885, for a discussion of Cooke's author attributions.
Unless otherwise noted, all entries with an identifying number or letter have an ink
to the left of the numeral or letter..

note.p: The sheets have been repaired, and places where text obliterated has been added back in pencil are indicated in the notes.

p.seg: The bottom left of the first sheet has been annotated by J. H. Willis '1 December 1886'. That sheet has at top left a pencil annotation, part of which is covered by a repair:

note.p: The list is arranged implicitly in five columns: reference number, Genus, species epithet and author, location, collector. This arrangement is formalised in this transcription.
